title: The.Hairy.Bikers-Pubs.That.Built.Britain--BBC-2016-w.subs-720p
description:
The Hairy Bikers' Pubs That Built Britain

The Hairy Bikers unearth hundreds of years of fascinating history hidden in Britain's boozers.

BBC (1026) - 15 Episodes
 
http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b078cqrp
_______________________________________

640x360 resolution

Video Codec h.264
Audio Codec AAC

With subtitles - enjoy !!
_______________________________________

    Yorkshire
    The Bikers visit a pub believed to have been drunk dry by troops in the English Civil War.

    The Lake District
    Dave takes Si on a pub tour of his Lake District home patch.

    Manchester
    Si and Dave visit a Manchester brewery to discover why beer became popular in Britain.

    Cornwall
    Si and Dave discover pubs that were at the centre of an illegal industry in the late 1700s

    Lincolnshire
    Si and Dave discover the importance of Bomber County's pubs during World War II.

    Liverpool
    The Hairy Bikers get groovy in Liverpool as they take a tour of some swinging 60s pubs.

    South Wales
    Dave unearths pubs that were at the heart of south Wales's coal-mining communities.

    Home Counties
    Si and Dave discover how Britain's inns and taverns witnessed the Wars of the Roses.

    Glasgow
    Si and Dave explore Glasgow's shipbuilding history.

    East End London
    Si and Dave step back in time to the 50s and 60s of London's East End.

    Edinburgh
    Si and Dave delve into the evil doings of Burke and Hare.

    Bristol
    The guys delve into Bristol's seafaring past and discover pubs with fascinating histories.

    Oxford
    Si visits Brasenose College for a taste of one of their ancient rituals.

    Great Fire of London
    Si and Dave's tour takes them to inns that witnessed the Great Fire of London.

    Carlisle
    The Hairy Bikers discover a WWI scheme designed to put a stop to drunken behaviour
